Data.event_text: 6 September  One of the largest fires occurs in Mount Bromo, East Java, following recklessly ignited flares.

links.text: -"Kebakaran di Gunung Bromo Padam Setelah 5 Hari". nasional (in Indonesian). Retrieved 2023-09-18.-

Data.event_text: 11 September - More than 3,500 people evacuates in Central Sulawesi following a strong 6.3 earthquake that struck the region.

links.text: -"Gempabumi M 6.3 Donggala, Sebanyak 3.780 Warga Mengungsi". BNPB. Retrieved 11 September 2023.-

Data.event_text: 16 September  The National Museum in Jakarta caught on fire in theGedung Gajahsection of the museum, causing the roof and the back walls of the building to collapse.

links.text: -"Museum Nasional Kebakaran, Bagian Belakang Bangunan Ambruk". kompas.com (in Indonesian). Retrieved 2023-08-16.-

Data.event_text: 21 September  Pohuwato regent office in Gorontalo is set alight by protesters who are demanding compensation for a gold mining. Previously, protesters have raided the office PT Puncak Tani Emas Sejahtera on the same day.

links.text: -"Demo Ganti Rugi Lahan Tambang Emas di Pohuwato Ricuh, Kantor Bupati Dibakar". detik.com. Retrieved 2023-09-21.-
-"Penambang Pohuwato Serbu Kantor PT PETS, Fasilitas dan Mobil Perusahaan Dirusak". tribunnews.com. Retrieved 2023-09-21.-

Data.event_text: 23 September - At least 3 are dead and more than a dozen are injured after a truck collides with multiple vehicles at a traffic intersection in Semarang.

links.text: -"Polisi Ungkap 16 Kendaraan dan Identitas Korban Meninggal Kecelakaan Simpang Tol Bawen". Republika. 24 September 2023. Retrieved 2 November 2023.-

Data.event_text: 25 September  TikTok Shop has been officially banned by the Ministry of Trade for trading in Indonesia.

links.text: -Hikam, Herdi Alif Al. "TikTok Shop cs Resmi Dilarang!". detikfinance (in Indonesian). Retrieved 2023-10-05.-

Data.event_text: 2 October - The Jakarta-Bandung Fast Train (KCJB) WHOOSH, the first high-speed train in Indonesia and Southeast Asia, is inaugurated by President Joko Widodo.

Data.event_text: 3 October - The Draft Law on State Civil Apparatus is passed by members of Indonesian House of Representatives and prohibits Government Agencies from recruiting Honorary Personnel.

links.text: -Arini, Shafira Cendra. "UU ASN 2023, Instansi Pemerintah Dilarang Rekrut Tenaga Honorer". detikfinance (in Indonesian). Retrieved 2023-10-05.-

Data.event_text: 13 October  The Corruption Eradication Commission names the Minister of Agriculture Syahrul Yasin Limpo as a suspect of a money laundering scheme within the Ministry of Agriculture.

links.text: -"KPK Ungkap Ada Aliran Uang Hasil Korupsi Syahrul Yasin Limpo ke Partai Nasdem Miliaran". Republika Online (in Indonesian). 2023-10-13. Retrieved 2023-10-16.-

Data.event_text: 16 October  The Constitutional Court of Indonesia rules that regional leaders under 40 may run for president or vice president, thus paving the path for President Joko Widodo's son, Gibran Rakabuming Raka, who is the mayor of Surakarta, to run as Vice President candidate in the next presidential election.

links.text: -"BREAKING: Constitutional Court opens door for Jokowi's son to run in presidential poll". The Jakarta Post. Retrieved 2023-10-16.-

Data.event_text: 17 October  At least 31 are injured after a passenger train collides with a derailed train in Kulonprogo, Yogyakarta.

links.text: -"31 Orang Terluka Akibat Anjloknya KA Semeru dan KA Argo Wilis". Republika. Retrieved 26 October 2023.-

Data.event_text: 18 October  Mahfud MD has been officially selected as vice presidential candidate to accompany presidential candidate Ganjar Pranowo in the 2024 Presidential Elections.

links.text: -"Mahfud MD resmi menjadi bakal cawapres pendamping Ganjar Pranowo". BBC News Indonesia (in Indonesian). 2023-10-18. Retrieved 2023-10-18.-
-Indonesia, C. N. N. "Mahfud MD Resmi Jadi Bakal Cawapres Ganjar Pranowo di Pilpres 2024". nasional (in Indonesian). Retrieved 2023-10-18.-

Data.event_text: 21 October - A tornado strikes a residential area in Sukabumi Regency, affecting over 300 residents and damaging more than 70 structures.

links.text: -"312 Orang Terdampak Angin Puting Beliung di Kabupaten Sukabumi". BNPB. Retrieved 21 October 2023.-

Data.event_text: 22 October  Prabowo Subianto has officially announced Gibran Rakabuming as vice presidential candidate in the 2024 Presidential Elections.

links.text: -Media, Kompas Cyber (2023-10-22). "Prabowo Resmi Umumkan Gibran Rakabuming Raka Jadi Cawapres". KOMPAS.com (in Indonesian). Retrieved 2023-10-30.-

Data.event_text: 24 October  Bali declares state of emergency over extreme drought and wildfires.

links.text: -"Kala Bali Siaga Darurat Kekeringan dan Kebakaran". Mongabay. Retrieved 26 October 2023.-

Data.event_text: 25 October  President Joko Widodo carries out a cabinet reshuffle with Arman Sulaiman as Minister of Agriculture, and also Lt. Gen. TNI Agus Subianto as Army Chief of Staff.

links.text: -"Presiden Jokowi Reshuffle Kabinet Hari Ini, Siapa?". SINDOnews Nasional (in Indonesian). Retrieved 2023-10-30.-

Data.event_text: 5 November  Following the blockade of Gaza by Israeli forces in response to the October 7 attack, multiple organizations, with support from the Indonesian government, hold a massive rally at Monas, Central Jakarta to show solidarity with the Palestinian cause.

links.text: -Wulandari (6 November 2023). "Fakta-Fakta Aksi Bela Palestina di Monas 5 November 2023". tirto.id (in Indonesian). Retrieved 2023-11-06.-
-"Aksi Bela Palestina di Monas, Hasilkan Enam Poin Sikap: Boikot Produk Israel hingga Ajakan Doa". Tribunnews.com (in Indonesian). 2023-11-05. Retrieved 2023-11-06.-

Data.event_text: 7 November  The Honorary Council of the Constitutional Court (MKMK) has decided to dismiss Anwar Usman as Chief Justice of the Constitutional Court for violating the Code of Ethics.

links.text: -"Putusan MKMK: Anwar Usman diberhentikan sebagai Ketua MK, terbukti melanggar kode etik berat". BBC News Indonesia (in Indonesian). 2023-11-07. Retrieved 2023-11-08.-

Data.event_text: 9 November  Suhartoyo is elected to become Chief Justice replacing Anwar Usman, who is also the brother-in-law of President Joko Widodo, after the Honor Council's decision to remove the latter from his position. This decision follows a controversial ruling regarding the age limit for presidential and vice-presidential candidates.

links.text: -"Constitutional Court Appoints Suhartoyo as New Chief Justice". Jakarta Globe. Retrieved 2023-11-09.-
-Hayat, Wiji Nur. "Suhartoyo Jadi Ketua MK Gantikan Anwar Usman, Ini Alasannya". CNBC Indonesia (in Indonesian). Retrieved 2023-11-22.-

Data.event_text: 10 November  2023 FIFA U-17 World Cup commences, with President Joko Widodo attending the opening ceremony.

links.text: -"2023 U-17 World Cup Opening Ceremony Commences Friday". Indonesia Expat. 10 November 2023. Retrieved 2023-11-14.-

Data.event_text: 12 November  Acting Sorong regent Yan Piet Mosso along with three officials of the Sorong Regency and two BPK examiners representative of Southwest Papua are arrested by the Corruption Eradication Commission.

links.text: -"Fakta-fakta PJ Bupati Sorong Ditangkap KPK". detik.com. Retrieved 2023-11-14.-

Data.event_text: 20 November  Indonesian language has been designated as the 10th Official Language at the General Conference of the United Nations (UN) Educational, General Scientific and Cultural Organization by UNESCO.

Data.event_text: 3 December  2023 eruption of Mount Marapi Eleven hikers are found dead and thirteen more are missing after Mount Marapi's eruption in West Sumatra.

links.text: -"Rescue mission continues as Indonesia volcano erupts, 12 still missing". CNA. Retrieved 2023-12-04.-

Data.event_text: 24 December  Thirteen workers are killed and 46 others are injured in a fire at a nickel smelter plant in Sulawesi.

links.text: -TAUFAN, MOHAMMAD. "Furnace explosion at Chinese-owned nickel plant in Indonesia kills at least 13 and injures 46 others". ABC News. Retrieved 2023-12-24.-

Data.event_text: 27 December  Hundreds of students from multiple universities across Aceh storms a shelter for Rohingya refugees and forces them out of a convention centre in the city of Banda Aceh, demanding them to be deported while chanting anti-refugee slurs. Following the incident, multiple international human rights organizations raises concerns on the matter.
